{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id56a18254-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"901"},"text":"§ 901.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Disposal of certain material","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56a18255-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Commandant subject to applicable regulations under subtitle I of title 40 and division C (except sections 3302, 3501(b), 3509, 3906, 4710, and 4711) of subtitle I of title 41 may dispose of, with or without charge, to the Coast Guard Auxiliary, including any incorporated unit thereof, to the sea-scout service of the Boy Scouts of America, and to any public body or private organization not organized for profit having an interest therein for historical or other special reasons, such obsolete or other material as may not be needed for the Coast Guard.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56a18256-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Commandant may, under regulations prescribed by the Secretary, sell apparatus or equipment manufactured by or in use in the Coast Guard, which is not readily procurable in the open market. The money received from such sale shall be deposited in the Treasury to the credit of the current appropriation from which purchase of similar apparatus or equipment is authorized.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56a18257-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id56a18258-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Commandant may—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id56a18259-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/c/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provide for the sale of recyclable materials that the Coast Guard holds;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id56a1825a-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/c/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provide for the operation of recycling programs at Coast Guard installations; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id56a1825b-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/c/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" designate Coast Guard installations that have qualified recycling programs for the purposes of subsection (d)(2).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id56a1825c-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Recyclable materials shall be sold in accordance with sections 541–555 of title 40, except that the Commandant may conduct sales of materials for which the proceeds of sale will not exceed $5,000 under regulations prescribed by the Commandant.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56a1825d-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id56a1825e-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Proceeds from the sale of recyclable materials at a Coast Guard installation shall be credited to funds available for operations and maintenance at that installation in amounts sufficient to cover operations, maintenance, recycling equipment, and overhead costs for processing recyclable materials at the installation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id56a1825f-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If, after funds are credited, a balance remains available to a Coast Guard installation and the installation has a qualified recycling program, not more than 50 percent of that balance may be used at the installation for projects for pollution abatement, energy conservation, and occupational safety and health activities. The cost of the project may not be greater than 50 percent of the amount permissible for a minor construction project.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id56a18260-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The remaining balance available to a Coast Guard installation may be transferred to the Coast Guard Morale, Welfare, and Recreation Program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56a18261-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s901/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If the balance available to the Coast Guard installation under this section at the end of a fiscal year is in excess of $200,000, the amount of that excess shall be deposited in the general fund of the Treasury as offsetting receipts of the Department in which the Coast Guard is operating and ascribed to Coast Guard activities.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id56a18262-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/547"},"text":"63 Stat. 547","children":[],"tail":", § 641; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1951-10-31/ch654/s2/11"},"text":"Oct. 31, 1951, ch. 654, § 2(11)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/65/707"},"text":"65 Stat. 707","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/295/s2/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–295, § 2(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1301"},"text":"96 Stat. 1301","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/587/tV/s5202"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–587, title V, § 5202","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-11-04"},"text":"Nov. 4, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/5071"},"text":"106 Stat. 5071","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/324/tIV/s408"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–324, title IV, § 408","children":[],"tail":", title XI, § 1119, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-19"},"text":"Oct. 19, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3925"},"text":"110 Stat. 3925","children":[],"tail":", 3973; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217/s3/c/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217, § 3(c)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1298"},"text":"116 Stat. 1298","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s5/c/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 5(c)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/3847"},"text":"124 Stat. 3847","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/120/tII/s209/10"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–120, title II, § 209(10)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-02-08"},"text":"Feb. 8, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/41"},"text":"130 Stat. 41","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 901, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/tI/s107/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 107(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-04"},"text":"Dec. 4, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/4205"},"text":"132 Stat. 4205","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id56a18263-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id56a18264-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (a) is based on title 14, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 43a (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1936-04-10/ch179"},"text":"Apr. 10, 1936, ch. 179","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/1195"},"text":"49 Stat. 1195","children":[],"tail":"). The authorization is enlarged to include any public body or private organization not organized for profit, and the authority to make disposal is placed in the Commandant rather than in the Secretary."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (b) is based on title 33, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 752a (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1926-05-22/ch371/s5"},"text":"May 22, 1926, ch. 371, § 5","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/626"},"text":"44 Stat. 626","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes were made in phraseology. 81st Congress, House Report No. 557.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id56a18265-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id56a18266-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s641"},"text":"section 641 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2016—Subsec. (d)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/120"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–120","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Guard installation” for “Guard, installation”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350","children":[],"tail":" substituted “division C (except sections 3302, 3501(b), 3509, 3906, 4710, and 4711) of subtitle I of title 41” for “title III of the Federal Property and Administrative Services Act of 1949 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s251"},"text":"41 U.S.C. 251","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217/s3/c/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217, § 3(c)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “subtitle I of title 40 and title III of” before “the Federal Property and Administrative Services Act of 1949” and substituted “("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s251"},"text":"41 U.S.C. 251","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)” for “("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s471"},"text":"40 U.S.C. 471","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217/s3/c/3/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217, § 3(c)(3)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “sections 541–555 of title 40” for “section 203 of the Federal Property and Administrative Services Act of 1949 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s484"},"text":"40 U.S.C. 484","children":[],"tail":")”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/324/s408"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–324, § 408","children":[],"tail":", inserted “to the Coast Guard Auxiliary, including any incorporated unit thereof,” after “with or without charge,” and struck out “to any incorporated unit of the Coast Guard Auxiliary,” after “Boy Scouts of America,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/324/s1119"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–324, § 1119","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, except that the Commandant may conduct sales of materials for which the proceeds of sale will not exceed $5,000 under regulations prescribed by the Commandant” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Subsecs. (c) to (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/587"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–587","children":[],"tail":" added subsecs. (c) to (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/295"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–295","children":[],"tail":" substituted “("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s471"},"text":"40 U.S.C. 471","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)” for “, as amended,” after “Act of 1949”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1951—Subsec. (a). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1951-10-31"},"text":"Oct. 31, 1951","children":[],"tail":", inserted reference to applicable regulations of the Federal Property and Administrative Services Act of 1949, as amended, and substituted “incorporated” for “regularly organized flotilla or other organized”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
